During this cold season, adding ginger to your soups can be a great way to boost your immunity while still getting the best of flavours. Ingredients • 1 tablespoon olive oil • 3 cups chopped carrots • 1 onion, chopped • 1 cup chopped butternut squash (or more carrots) • 2 garlic cloves, minced • 1 tablespoon grated ginger (about 2" piece) • 1 tablespoon turmeric powder • Salt and pepper to taste • 3 cups low sodium vegetable broth • 1 (14.5 oz) can lite coconut milk Preparation Step 1 Heat the olive oil in a large pan. Add the onions, carrots, and squash. Saute for 3 - 5 minutes until the veggies start to soften. Step 2 Add the garlic, ginger, turmeric, salt, and pepper, and saute for a few more minutes. Add the broth and coconut milk. Bring the mixture to a boil, cover and simmer for 20 minutes. Step 3 Once the soup is cooked, add it to a blender and blend until creamy. You could also use an immersion blender. Taste and adjust seasonings to your taste. Step 4 Serve immediately with a dollop of coconut yoghurt and enjoy with your favourite bread.